c-1 0-1.2.5-1.2 1.3v1.8h3l-.1 2.8z"></path></svg></span></a></li><li class="css-h50b31"><a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Nvidia%20Shield%20TV%20review%3A%20the%20best%20Android%20TV%20box%20with%20brilliant%20AI%20upscaling&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Ftechnology%2F2020%2Ffeb%2F26%2Fnvidia-shield-tv-review-the-best-android-tv-box-with-brilliant-ai-upscaling&amp;CMP=share_btn_tw" role="button" aria-label="Share on Twitter"><span class="css-1adb3ql"><svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="-2 -2 32 32"><path d="M21.3 10.5v.5c0 4.7-3.5 10.1-9.9 10.1-2 0-3.8-.6-5.3-1.6.3 0 .6.1.8.1 1.6 0 3.1-.6 4.3-1.5-1.5 0-2.8-1-3.3-2.4.2 0 .4.1.7.1l.9-.1c-1.6-.3-2.8-1.8-2.8-3.5.5.3 1 .4 1.6.4-.9-.6-1.6-1.7-1.6-2.9 0-.6.2-1.3.5-1.8 1.7 2.1 4.3 3.6 7.2 3.7-.1-.3-.1-.5-.1-.8 0-2 1.6-3.5 3.5-3.5 1 0 1.9.4 2.5 1.1.8-.1 1.5-.4 2.2-.8-.3.8-.8 1.5-1.5 1.9.7-.1 1.4-.3 2-.5-.4.4-1 1-1.7 1.5z"></path></svg></span></a></li><li class="css-h50b31"><a href="mailto:?subject=Nvidia%20Shield%20TV%20review%3A%20the%20best%20Android%20TV%20box%20with%20brilliant%20AI%20upscaling&amp;body=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Ftechnology%2F2020%2Ffeb%2F26%2Fnvidia-shield-tv-review-the-best-android-tv-box-with-brilliant-ai-upscaling&amp;CMP=share_btn_link" role="button" aria-label="Share via Email"><span class="css-1adb3ql"><svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 32 32"><path d="M23.363 20.875H8.637v-8.938l6.545 5.687h1.637l6.544-5.687v8.938zm-1.635-9.75L16 16l-5.728-4.875h11.456zM23.363 9.5H8.637L7 11.125v9.75L8.637 22.5h14.727L25 20.875v-9.75L23.363 9.5z"></path></svg></span></a></li></ul></div><div class="css-eaqpiw"><div id="share-comment-counts"></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="css-1uuhxtj"><main class="css-sgtam6"><main class="css-myhfeo"><div class="css-avj6db"><div class="article-body-commercial-selector css-79elbk"><p class="css-38z03z"><span class="css-17ehqsd"><span class="css-jwwgxz">T</span></span><span class="css-38z03z">he Nvidia Shield TV is a refined version of the best <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/android" data-component="auto-linked-tag" data-link-name="in body link">Android</a> TV box for years, packed with impressive new AI-based upscaling technology and a novel space-saving design.</span></p><p class="css-38z03z">The new Nvidia Shield TV comes in two versions: a £149.99 media streamer and a “Pro” alternative for £199 that is aimed more at gaming.</p><span id="sign-in-gate"></span><p class="css-38z03z">For those unfamiliar with these types of media streaming devices, they in effect add a smart TV experience to older televisions or replace the often terrible or out-of-date smart elements of more modern sets, so that you can use apps such as Amazon Prime Video, BBC iPlayer and Netflix.</p><p class="css-38z03z">Nvidia is arguably the biggest name in graphics, and also makes mobile chips called Tegra, on which these two Android TV boxes are based. The previous Shield was released in 2015 and, unlike many other smart TVs and streaming boxes, is being kept fresh with a steady stream of updates, making it the best, most supported Android TV experience available either baked into a TV or in a set-top box.</p><p class="css-38z03z">The new Shield TV doesn’t mess with the formula. You get one of the most powerful media-streaming boxes available, running the latest version of Android TV and similar long-term software support.</p><h2 class="">User-centric design</h2><div class="css-10khgmf"><div class="css-1nfcn93"><picture><!--[if IE 9]><video style="display: none;"><![endif]--> <source media="(min-width: 620px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 620px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="620px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/7892dd2b98b4d0f7da5a535fa90cc62b5f44e8f4/998_563_2977_1786/master/2977.jpg?width=620&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=98c4c01d1f6d2a0559f85864bf129c27 1240w"/> <source media="(min-width: 620px)" sizes="620px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/7892dd2b98b4d0f7da5a535fa90cc62b5f44e8f4/998_563_2977_1786/master/2977.jpg?width=620&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=98c4c01d1f6d2a0559f85864bf129c27 620w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1240px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 1240px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="1240px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/7892dd2b98b4d0f7da5a535fa90cc62b5f44e8f4/998_563_2977_1786/master/2977.jpg?width=620&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=a8561525f8328e2c240903368987b91e 2480w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1240px)" sizes="1240px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/7892dd2b98b4d0f7da5a535fa90cc62b5f44e8f4/998_563_2977_1786/master/2977.jpg?width=620&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=a8561525f8328e2c240903368987b91e 1240w"/> <source media="(min-width: 605px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 605px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="605px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/7892dd2b98b4d0f7da5a535fa90cc62b5f44e8f4/998_563_2977_1786/master/2977.jpg?width=605&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=8c45897cca5ef12de77afdfb0c14cca2 1210w"/> <source media="(min-width: 605px)" sizes="605px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/7892dd2b98b4d0f7da5a535fa90cc62b5f44e8f4/998_563_2977_1786/master/2977.jpg?width=605&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=8c45897cca5ef12de77afdfb0c14cca2 605w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1210px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 1210px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="1210px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/7892dd2b98b4d0f7da5a535fa90cc62b5f44e8f4/998_563_2977_1786/master/2977.jpg?width=605&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=c7a44522cdb24a9a68160befb5957ba6 2420w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1210px)" sizes="1210px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/7892dd2b98b4d0f7da5a535fa90cc62b5f44e8f4/998_563_2977_1786/master/2977.jpg?width=605&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=c7a44522cdb24a9a68160befb5957ba6 1210w"/> <source media="(min-width: 445px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 445px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="445px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/7892dd2b98b4d0f7da5a535fa90cc62b5f44e8f4/998_563_2977_1786/master/2977.jpg?width=445&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=a79d61291701dc673c0f219e4071edde 890w"/> <source media="(min-width: 445px)" sizes="445px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/7892dd2b98b4d0f7da5a535fa90cc62b5f44e8f4/998_563_2977_1786/master/2977.jpg?width=445&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=a79d61291701dc673c0f219e4071edde 445w"/> <source media="(min-width: 890px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 890px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="890px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/7892dd2b98b4d0f7da5a535fa90cc62b5f44e8f4/998_563_2977_1786/master/2977.jpg?width=445&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=f9f1676b814e048b1fe2902b164542dd 1780w"/> <source media="(min-width: 890px)" sizes="890px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/7892dd2b98b4d0f7da5a535fa90cc62b5f44e8f4/998_563_2977_1786/master/2977.jpg?width=445&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=f9f1676b814e048b1fe2902b164542dd 890w"/><!--[if IE 9]></video><![endif]--><img style="vertical-align: middle;" itemprop="contentUrl" alt="Nvidia Shield TV remote control" src="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/7892dd2b98b4d0f7da5a535fa90cc62b5f44e8f4/998_563_2977_1786/master/2977.jpg?width=445&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=a79d61291701dc673c0f219e4071edde" height="1786" width="2977" loading="lazy"/></picture></div><figcaption class="css-xe26t6"><span class="css-1amgqzt"><svg width="11" height="10" viewBox="0 0 11 10"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.5 0L11 10H0z"/></svg></span><span class="css-19x4pdv">The triangular remote looks odd at first glance, but works really well and won’t slip around or get lost down the side of the sofa.</span> Photograph: Samuel Gibbs/The Guardian</figcaption></div><p class="css-38z03z">What’s new is the form factor. The standard Shield TV is not a box but a small tube with a power cable and ethernet socket in one end and an HDMI socket and microSD card slot in the other. The idea is you hide this small tube behind your TV in series with the cable without taking up any significant space.</p><p class="css-38z03z">The remote too has been rethought. Instead of being a thin, touch-sensitive remote, the new version has a triangular profile, takes two standard AAA batteries including rechargeables, has a good weight to it and an assortment of buttons that are backlit when the remote is picked up, including dedicated pause and volume buttons.</p><p class="css-38z03z">The shape may seem odd but it’s designed to prevent it slipping down the side or backs of sofas, and it works. A simple, user-friendly design.</p><p class="css-38z03z">The remote communicates with the Shield TV via Bluetooth and has an IR blaster in the end for controlling the volume on your TV, amp or soundbar. It works great.</p><h2 class="">Specifications</h2><ul class="css-38z03z">
<li><p><strong>Processor:</strong> Nvidia Tegra X1+</p></li>
<li><p><strong>RAM:</strong> 2 or 3GB</p></li>
<li><p><strong>Storage:</strong> 8 or 16GB + microSD card</p></li>
<li><p><strong>Connectivity:</strong> wifi ac, Bluetooth 5, gigabit ethernet, HDMI 2.0b (HDCP2.2), 2x USB 3.0 (Pro only)</p></li>
<li><p><strong>Software:</strong> Android TV (Android 9 Pie)</p></li>
<li><p><strong>Format support:</strong> up to 4K @ 60Hz, Dolby Vision, HDR10, Dolby Atmos, TrueHD and Digital Plus, DTS-X</p></li>
<li><p><strong>Dimensions:</strong> 40mm diameter, 165mm length or 98 x 159 x 259.3mm</p></li>
<li><p><strong>Weight:</strong> 137g or 250g</p></li>
</ul><h2 class="">Android TV</h2><div class="css-10khgmf"><div class="css-1nfcn93"><picture><!--[if IE 9]><video style="display: none;"><![endif]--> <source media="(min-width: 620px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 620px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="620px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/52b4d9da88499cb59b4855c34fd4046b47336399/291_299_4331_2599/master/4331.jpg?width=620&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=5018830cc0e2dc577f34d7e240ee3313 1240w"/> <source media="(min-width: 620px)" sizes="620px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/52b4d9da88499cb59b4855c34fd4046b47336399/291_299_4331_2599/master/4331.jpg?width=620&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=5018830cc0e2dc577f34d7e240ee3313 620w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1240px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 1240px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="1240px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/52b4d9da88499cb59b4855c34fd4046b47336399/291_299_4331_2599/master/4331.jpg?width=620&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=f461685024ece4362b148d5b452db439 2480w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1240px)" sizes="1240px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/52b4d9da88499cb59b4855c34fd4046b47336399/291_299_4331_2599/master/4331.jpg?width=620&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=f461685024ece4362b148d5b452db439 1240w"/> <source media="(min-width: 605px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 605px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="605px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/52b4d9da88499cb59b4855c34fd4046b47336399/291_299_4331_2599/master/4331.jpg?width=605&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=f13568fefdb05895bd53dc41902dfab6 1210w"/> <source media="(min-width: 605px)" sizes="605px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/52b4d9da88499cb59b4855c34fd4046b47336399/291_299_4331_2599/master/4331.jpg?width=605&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=f13568fefdb05895bd53dc41902dfab6 605w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1210px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 1210px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="1210px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/52b4d9da88499cb59b4855c34fd4046b47336399/291_299_4331_2599/master/4331.jpg?width=605&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=5ab3b84d2aa03009a6c323cdd0c910e8 2420w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1210px)" sizes="1210px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/52b4d9da88499cb59b4855c34fd4046b47336399/291_299_4331_2599/master/4331.jpg?width=605&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=5ab3b84d2aa03009a6c323cdd0c910e8 1210w"/> <source media="(min-width: 445px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 445px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="445px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/52b4d9da88499cb59b4855c34fd4046b47336399/291_299_4331_2599/master/4331.jpg?width=445&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=ccb42d03dea0654ea17ed79f7d772cd3 890w"/> <source media="(min-width: 445px)" sizes="445px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/52b4d9da88499cb59b4855c34fd4046b47336399/291_299_4331_2599/master/4331.jpg?width=445&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=ccb42d03dea0654ea17ed79f7d772cd3 445w"/> <source media="(min-width: 890px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 890px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="890px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/52b4d9da88499cb59b4855c34fd4046b47336399/291_299_4331_2599/master/4331.jpg?width=445&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=e086805a67e2a6a58c3b90ce1b53a15b 1780w"/> <source media="(min-width: 890px)" sizes="890px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/52b4d9da88499cb59b4855c34fd4046b47336399/291_299_4331_2599/master/4331.jpg?width=445&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=e086805a67e2a6a58c3b90ce1b53a15b 890w"/><!--[if IE 9]></video><![endif]--><img style="vertical-align: middle;" itemprop="contentUrl" alt="Nvidia Shield TV interface" src="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/52b4d9da88499cb59b4855c34fd4046b47336399/291_299_4331_2599/master/4331.jpg?width=445&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=ccb42d03dea0654ea17ed79f7d772cd3" height="2599" width="4331" loading="lazy"/></picture></div><figcaption class="css-xe26t6"><span class="css-1amgqzt"><svg width="11" height="10" viewBox="0 0 11 10"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.5 0L11 10H0z"/></svg></span><span class="css-19x4pdv">The Shield TV has is the standard, customisable Android TV interface, without adverts, with a few Nvidia additions for things such as the AI upscaling, GeForce Now game streaming and accessory updates.</span> Photograph: Samuel Gibbs/The Guardian</figcaption></div><p class="css-38z03z">Google’s Android TV platform is a fairly simple system based on apps and a customisable carousel layout that highlights content from certain apps. On the Shield TV it’s fast and easy to navigate in a way it often isn’t on smart TVs.</p><p class="css-38z03z">Getting around the interface is straightforward with the home, back and up, down, left and right buttons in a ring around the select button. Holding the home button pops up a quick access a list of apps, while double-pressing home takes you to recently used apps like on a smartphone or tablet.</p><p class="css-38z03z">Holding the back button brings up quick access to the settings menu, while the menu button in the top right can be customised to launch particular apps, settings or functions. There’s even a dedicated Netflix button for jumping straight in.</p><div class="css-10khgmf"><div class="css-1nfcn93"><picture><!--[if IE 9]><video style="display: none;"><![endif]--> <source media="(min-width: 620px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 620px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="620px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c38c3efeb71dd951eec08a020daf082b7a6b409d/617_520_3714_2229/master/3714.jpg?width=620&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=9aaa0471334d02622a6368384e181104 1240w"/> <source media="(min-width: 620px)" sizes="620px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c38c3efeb71dd951eec08a020daf082b7a6b409d/617_520_3714_2229/master/3714.jpg?width=620&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=9aaa0471334d02622a6368384e181104 620w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1240px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 1240px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="1240px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c38c3efeb71dd951eec08a020daf082b7a6b409d/617_520_3714_2229/master/3714.jpg?width=620&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=a9ca898e8a8c783bb0a528f20203b457 2480w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1240px)" sizes="1240px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c38c3efeb71dd951eec08a020daf082b7a6b409d/617_520_3714_2229/master/3714.jpg?width=620&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=a9ca898e8a8c783bb0a528f20203b457 1240w"/> <source media="(min-width: 605px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 605px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="605px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c38c3efeb71dd951eec08a020daf082b7a6b409d/617_520_3714_2229/master/3714.jpg?width=605&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=aa91fe4b92093892bdbec478dab2ab0a 1210w"/> <source media="(min-width: 605px)" sizes="605px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c38c3efeb71dd951eec08a020daf082b7a6b409d/617_520_3714_2229/master/3714.jpg?width=605&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=aa91fe4b92093892bdbec478dab2ab0a 605w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1210px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 1210px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="1210px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c38c3efeb71dd951eec08a020daf082b7a6b409d/617_520_3714_2229/master/3714.jpg?width=605&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=646c49088ae8ecb34101b4e443705352 2420w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1210px)" sizes="1210px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c38c3efeb71dd951eec08a020daf082b7a6b409d/617_520_3714_2229/master/3714.jpg?width=605&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=646c49088ae8ecb34101b4e443705352 1210w"/> <source media="(min-width: 445px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 445px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="445px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c38c3efeb71dd951eec08a020daf082b7a6b409d/617_520_3714_2229/master/3714.jpg?width=445&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=5281d0bcfcd740dfc0e075b118816403 890w"/> <source media="(min-width: 445px)" sizes="445px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c38c3efeb71dd951eec08a020daf082b7a6b409d/617_520_3714_2229/master/3714.jpg?width=445&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=5281d0bcfcd740dfc0e075b118816403 445w"/> <source media="(min-width: 890px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 890px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="890px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c38c3efeb71dd951eec08a020daf082b7a6b409d/617_520_3714_2229/master/3714.jpg?width=445&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=36771565f1a7e309d8d241ccf377553d 1780w"/> <source media="(min-width: 890px)" sizes="890px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c38c3efeb71dd951eec08a020daf082b7a6b409d/617_520_3714_2229/master/3714.jpg?width=445&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=36771565f1a7e309d8d241ccf377553d 890w"/><!--[if IE 9]></video><![endif]--><img style="vertical-align: middle;" itemprop="contentUrl" alt="The Nvidia Shield TV tube" src="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c38c3efeb71dd951eec08a020daf082b7a6b409d/617_520_3714_2229/master/3714.jpg?width=445&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=5281d0bcfcd740dfc0e075b118816403" height="2229" width="3714" loading="lazy"/></picture></div><figcaption class="css-xe26t6"><span class="css-1amgqzt"><svg width="11" height="10" viewBox="0 0 11 10"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.5 0L11 10H0z"/></svg></span><span class="css-19x4pdv">The tube has an HDMI socket and microSD card slot in one end.</span> Photograph: Samuel Gibbs/The Guardian</figcaption></div><p class="css-38z03z">One of the biggest advantages Android TV has compared to other systems built into TVs is the wide app support from most of the major UK and US streaming services. Google Play, Amazon Prime Video, Netflix, YouTube, BBC iPlayer, ITV Hub, All 4, My5 and Spotify are available, with the two notable exceptions being BT Sport (although BT TV is available) and the Apple TV app. Plex Media Server support is limited to the Pro model of Shield TV.</p><p class="css-38z03z">The apps are routinely updated too, meaning they continue to work, unlike some other platforms, which combined with Nvidia’s long support means you get a streaming box that should stand the test of time.</p><p class="css-38z03z">Alongside direct app support, the Shield TV has Chromecast 4K support built in, which means any app that can be cast from your Android or iPhone, tablet or even computer can be sent to your screen wirelessly, which includes BT Sport but not Apple TV.</p><p class="css-38z03z">Apps other than TV and video streaming services are also available, including Android games and Nvidia’s GeForce Now game-streaming service, which has both paid and free tiers of PC games and works surprisingly well. You’ll need a controller for games, and while Nvidia sells one, you can use any Xbox or PlayStation joypad that supports Bluetooth.</p><h2 class="">Google Assistant</h2><div class="css-10khgmf"><div class="css-1nfcn93"><picture><!--[if IE 9]><video style="display: none;"><![endif]--> <source media="(min-width: 620px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 620px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="620px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/5ace1320357657afeaf620bbb3c4ac0e447c8fa3/0_86_4928_2957/master/4928.jpg?width=620&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=82a19066288869a10bf32e1881fbe917 1240w"/> <source media="(min-width: 620px)" sizes="620px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/5ace1320357657afeaf620bbb3c4ac0e447c8fa3/0_86_4928_2957/master/4928.jpg?width=620&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=82a19066288869a10bf32e1881fbe917 620w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1240px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 1240px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="1240px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/5ace1320357657afeaf620bbb3c4ac0e447c8fa3/0_86_4928_2957/master/4928.jpg?width=620&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=1921b5356654f79e46d9ef9bcf74cefd 2480w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1240px)" sizes="1240px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/5ace1320357657afeaf620bbb3c4ac0e447c8fa3/0_86_4928_2957/master/4928.jpg?width=620&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=1921b5356654f79e46d9ef9bcf74cefd 1240w"/> <source media="(min-width: 605px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 605px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="605px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/5ace1320357657afeaf620bbb3c4ac0e447c8fa3/0_86_4928_2957/master/4928.jpg?width=605&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=3b44c3fa49abf66ac9822ae40779d1fb 1210w"/> <source media="(min-width: 605px)" sizes="605px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/5ace1320357657afeaf620bbb3c4ac0e447c8fa3/0_86_4928_2957/master/4928.jpg?width=605&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=3b44c3fa49abf66ac9822ae40779d1fb 605w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1210px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 1210px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="1210px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/5ace1320357657afeaf620bbb3c4ac0e447c8fa3/0_86_4928_2957/master/4928.jpg?width=605&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=00ad54d9c9b68b14b2f689aca1f3ea74 2420w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1210px)" sizes="1210px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/5ace1320357657afeaf620bbb3c4ac0e447c8fa3/0_86_4928_2957/master/4928.jpg?width=605&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=00ad54d9c9b68b14b2f689aca1f3ea74 1210w"/> <source media="(min-width: 445px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 445px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="445px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/5ace1320357657afeaf620bbb3c4ac0e447c8fa3/0_86_4928_2957/master/4928.jpg?width=445&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=cac8060d375400002c60da271d08379e 890w"/> <source media="(min-width: 445px)" sizes="445px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/5ace1320357657afeaf620bbb3c4ac0e447c8fa3/0_86_4928_2957/master/4928.jpg?width=445&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=cac8060d375400002c60da271d08379e 445w"/> <source media="(min-width: 890px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 890px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="890px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/5ace1320357657afeaf620bbb3c4ac0e447c8fa3/0_86_4928_2957/master/4928.jpg?width=445&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=2f75f0bbd719fa29eeadb38def2a3977 1780w"/> <source media="(min-width: 890px)" sizes="890px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/5ace1320357657afeaf620bbb3c4ac0e447c8fa3/0_86_4928_2957/master/4928.jpg?width=445&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=2f75f0bbd719fa29eeadb38def2a3977 890w"/><!--[if IE 9]></video><![endif]--><img style="vertical-align: middle;" itemprop="contentUrl" alt="The Nvidia Shield TV remote" src="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/5ace1320357657afeaf620bbb3c4ac0e447c8fa3/0_86_4928_2957/master/4928.jpg?width=445&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=cac8060d375400002c60da271d08379e" height="2957" width="4928" loading="lazy"/></picture></div><figcaption class="css-xe26t6"><span class="css-1amgqzt"><svg width="11" height="10" viewBox="0 0 11 10"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.5 0L11 10H0z"/></svg></span><span class="css-19x4pdv">Press and hold the mic button on the remote to talk to Google Assistant.</span> Photograph: Samuel Gibbs/The Guardian</figcaption></div><p class="css-38z03z">Google Assistant is built into Android TV and works like a cross between an Android phone and a smart display such as the <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2019/nov/06/google-nest-hub-max-review-display-camera-facial-recognition" data-link-name="in body link">Nest Hub Max</a>. Press and hold the mic button on the remote to talk to Assistant.</p><p class="css-38z03z">You can control playback in apps, such as playing, pausing or skipping to the next track in Spotify or even a particular time in a song, movie or TV show. You can launch apps, adjust the volume or search for shows, movies or tracks via voice. Ask Assistant to play <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2018/apr/13/lost-in-space-review-netflix" data-link-name="in body link">Lost in Space</a> and it will offer to play it via Netflix or Google Play Movies.</p><p class="css-38z03z">Then there are all the standard Assistant functions. Ask it how to get to work and it’ll give you the current state of traffic or transport and a small map. Ask it for the weather and you’ll get the forecast with visual cards. It’ll answer questions, command smart home devices, stream footage from smart cameras and hundreds of other things. The only exception I found was an inability to search for images from the web.</p><h2 class="">Next-generation AI upscaling</h2><div class="css-10khgmf"><div class="css-1nfcn93"><picture><!--[if IE 9]><video style="display: none;"><![endif]--> <source media="(min-width: 620px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 620px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="620px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/ce6244a3ca93273134a79ae270128598b1c1def2/578_466_3841_2305/master/3841.jpg?width=620&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=955ebebec9236974735af6f08dfc9489 1240w"/> <source media="(min-width: 620px)" sizes="620px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/ce6244a3ca93273134a79ae270128598b1c1def2/578_466_3841_2305/master/3841.jpg?width=620&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=955ebebec9236974735af6f08dfc9489 620w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1240px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 1240px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="1240px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/ce6244a3ca93273134a79ae270128598b1c1def2/578_466_3841_2305/master/3841.jpg?width=620&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=3cfc5bd6357e2ff9d190889bff600da9 2480w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1240px)" sizes="1240px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/ce6244a3ca93273134a79ae270128598b1c1def2/578_466_3841_2305/master/3841.jpg?width=620&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=3cfc5bd6357e2ff9d190889bff600da9 1240w"/> <source media="(min-width: 605px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 605px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="605px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/ce6244a3ca93273134a79ae270128598b1c1def2/578_466_3841_2305/master/3841.jpg?width=605&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=f44a09df7baf01250996920e1b0331d4 1210w"/> <source media="(min-width: 605px)" sizes="605px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/ce6244a3ca93273134a79ae270128598b1c1def2/578_466_3841_2305/master/3841.jpg?width=605&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=f44a09df7baf01250996920e1b0331d4 605w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1210px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 1210px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="1210px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/ce6244a3ca93273134a79ae270128598b1c1def2/578_466_3841_2305/master/3841.jpg?width=605&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=ef2687e0638f14b99e8f8980895d797b 2420w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1210px)" sizes="1210px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/ce6244a3ca93273134a79ae270128598b1c1def2/578_466_3841_2305/master/3841.jpg?width=605&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=ef2687e0638f14b99e8f8980895d797b 1210w"/> <source media="(min-width: 445px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 445px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="445px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/ce6244a3ca93273134a79ae270128598b1c1def2/578_466_3841_2305/master/3841.jpg?width=445&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=353b89595f6c32efa3d084d1fe874ee3 890w"/> <source media="(min-width: 445px)" sizes="445px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/ce6244a3ca93273134a79ae270128598b1c1def2/578_466_3841_2305/master/3841.jpg?width=445&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=353b89595f6c32efa3d084d1fe874ee3 445w"/> <source media="(min-width: 890px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 890px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="890px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/ce6244a3ca93273134a79ae270128598b1c1def2/578_466_3841_2305/master/3841.jpg?width=445&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=8641a7b75bdf67cd2e8b9cd7f7e0285c 1780w"/> <source media="(min-width: 890px)" sizes="890px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/ce6244a3ca93273134a79ae270128598b1c1def2/578_466_3841_2305/master/3841.jpg?width=445&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=8641a7b75bdf67cd2e8b9cd7f7e0285c 890w"/><!--[if IE 9]></video><![endif]--><img style="vertical-align: middle;" itemprop="contentUrl" alt="The Nvidia Shield TV" src="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/ce6244a3ca93273134a79ae270128598b1c1def2/578_466_3841_2305/master/3841.jpg?width=445&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=353b89595f6c32efa3d084d1fe874ee3" height="2305" width="3841" loading="lazy"/></picture></div><figcaption class="css-xe26t6"><span class="css-1amgqzt"><svg width="11" height="10" viewBox="0 0 11 10"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.5 0L11 10H0z"/></svg></span><span class="css-19x4pdv">Nvidia’s AI-powered HD-to-4K upscaling technology is very impressive, and ideal for dealing with the many shows and movies across the various UK TV catchup services, Netflix, Amazon and Google Play that are still in HD.</span> Photograph: Samuel Gibbs/The Guardian</figcaption></div><p class="css-38z03z">The Shield TV’s ace in the hole is Nvidia’s new AI upscaling technology, which takes HD content and turns it into 4K with some very impressive results. While practically every TV or set-top box can handle basic upscaling of content – stretching HD content to fit a 4K screen with four times as many pixels – Nvidia’s technology is a cut above, particularly when viewing highly detailed scenes.</p><p class="css-38z03z">Cityscapes look incredibly crisp and detailed, while faces, cars and even wildlife are all significantly improved even compared to basic upscaling. Feed it a modern HD picture and the differences between it and real 4K content are surprisingly hard to spot. It even makes a decent job of handling something as old as NCIS, Futurama or Knight Rider.</p><p class="css-38z03z">Only comparing something such as the faces of Will Smith and Martin Lawrence in Bad Boys in proper 4K versus the HD AI-upscaled version can you begin to spot the differences in closeup scenes or when the original picture was a little grainy in low light.</p><h2 class="">Observations</h2><div class="css-10khgmf"><div class="css-1nfcn93"><picture><!--[if IE 9]><video style="display: none;"><![endif]--> <source media="(min-width: 620px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 620px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="620px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/4d7ca448d40c864e1c60047cfa935c44d4b58a75/648_670_3677_2206/master/3677.jpg?width=620&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=0e71a43952f3414fa3dde5a74422fdf6 1240w"/> <source media="(min-width: 620px)" sizes="620px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/4d7ca448d40c864e1c60047cfa935c44d4b58a75/648_670_3677_2206/master/3677.jpg?width=620&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=0e71a43952f3414fa3dde5a74422fdf6 620w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1240px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 1240px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="1240px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/4d7ca448d40c864e1c60047cfa935c44d4b58a75/648_670_3677_2206/master/3677.jpg?width=620&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=3847f28c74958e5b44980fb7cf7a7f2c 2480w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1240px)" sizes="1240px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/4d7ca448d40c864e1c60047cfa935c44d4b58a75/648_670_3677_2206/master/3677.jpg?width=620&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=3847f28c74958e5b44980fb7cf7a7f2c 1240w"/> <source media="(min-width: 605px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 605px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="605px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/4d7ca448d40c864e1c60047cfa935c44d4b58a75/648_670_3677_2206/master/3677.jpg?width=605&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=3d6c1b2b31d6eb6317c8db12d4f2024f 1210w"/> <source media="(min-width: 605px)" sizes="605px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/4d7ca448d40c864e1c60047cfa935c44d4b58a75/648_670_3677_2206/master/3677.jpg?width=605&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=3d6c1b2b31d6eb6317c8db12d4f2024f 605w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1210px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 1210px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="1210px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/4d7ca448d40c864e1c60047cfa935c44d4b58a75/648_670_3677_2206/master/3677.jpg?width=605&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=ae67127d9f6882521354c7c680da6874 2420w"/> <source media="(min-width: 1210px)" sizes="1210px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/4d7ca448d40c864e1c60047cfa935c44d4b58a75/648_670_3677_2206/master/3677.jpg?width=605&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=ae67127d9f6882521354c7c680da6874 1210w"/> <source media="(min-width: 445px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 445px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="445px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/4d7ca448d40c864e1c60047cfa935c44d4b58a75/648_670_3677_2206/master/3677.jpg?width=445&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=bb329c0e2d0bb7c63c331c65ec775f9b 890w"/> <source media="(min-width: 445px)" sizes="445px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/4d7ca448d40c864e1c60047cfa935c44d4b58a75/648_670_3677_2206/master/3677.jpg?width=445&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=bb329c0e2d0bb7c63c331c65ec775f9b 445w"/> <source media="(min-width: 890px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.25), (min-width: 890px) and (min-resolution: 120dpi)" sizes="890px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/4d7ca448d40c864e1c60047cfa935c44d4b58a75/648_670_3677_2206/master/3677.jpg?width=445&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=9e29bd01d310bd2fe393f40a033a7ec1 1780w"/> <source media="(min-width: 890px)" sizes="890px" srcset="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/4d7ca448d40c864e1c60047cfa935c44d4b58a75/648_670_3677_2206/master/3677.jpg?width=445&quality=45&auto=format&fit=max&dpr=2&s=9e29bd01d310bd2fe393f40a033a7ec1 890w"/><!--[if IE 9]></video><![endif]--><img style="vertical-align: middle;" itemprop="contentUrl" alt="The Nvidia Shield TV tube" src="https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/4d7ca448d40c864e1c60047cfa935c44d4b58a75/648_670_3677_2206/master/3677.jpg?width=445&quality=85&auto=format&fit=max&s=bb329c0e2d0bb7c63c331c65ec775f9b" height="2206" width="3677" loading="lazy"/></picture></div><figcaption class="css-xe26t6"><span class="css-1amgqzt"><svg width="11" height="10" viewBox="0 0 11 10"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.5 0L11 10H0z"/></svg></span><span class="css-19x4pdv">The standard figure-of-eight power lead and optional ethernet plug into the other end of the tube.</span> Photograph: Samuel Gibbs/The Guardian</figcaption></div><ul class="css-38z03z">
<li><p>You can play music in the background from Spotify or similar while doing other things.</p></li>
<li><p>The Shield TV can be controlled through Alexa on an Echo smart speaker via the Nvidia Shield TV skill.</p></li>
<li><p>The Shield TV comes with a two-year warranty, but Nvidia doesn’t currently offer a repair, recycling or trade-in programme, ultimately making it disposable.</p></li>
</ul><h2 class="">Price</h2><p class="css-38z03z">The Nvidia Shield TV costs <a href="http://go.theguardian.com/?id=114047X1572903&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nvidia.com%2Fen-gb%2Fshield%2Fshield-tv%2F&amp;sref=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2020/feb/26/nvidia-shield-tv-review-the-best-android-tv-box-with-brilliant-ai-upscaling" data-link-name="in body link">£149.99</a> while the Shield TV Pro costs <a href="http://go.theguardian.com/?id=114047X1572903&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nvidia.com%2Fen-gb%2Fshield%2Fshield-tv-pro%2F&amp;sref=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2020/feb/26/nvidia-shield-tv-review-the-best-android-tv-box-with-brilliant-ai-upscaling" data-link-name="in body link">£199</a>. The optional Shield Controller costs <a href="http://go.theguardian.com/?id=114047X1572903&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nvidia.com%2Fen-gb%2Fshield%2Fbuy%2F&amp;sref=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2020/feb/26/nvidia-shield-tv-review-the-best-android-tv-box-with-brilliant-ai-upscaling" data-link-name="in body link">£59.99</a>.</p><p class="css-38z03z">For comparison, Amazon’s Fire TV Stick 4K costs <a href="http://go.theguardian.com/?id=114047X1572903&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.co.uk%2Fdp%2FB079QB9BD7%2F&amp;sref=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2020/feb/26/nvidia-shield-tv-review-the-best-android-tv-box-with-brilliant-ai-upscaling" data-link-name="in body link">£49.99</a>, <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2020/jan/09/amazon-fire-tv-cube-review-great-smart-tv-box-irritating-smart-speaker" data-link-name="in body link">Fire TV Cube</a> costs <a href="http://go.theguardian.com/?id=114047X1572903&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.co.uk%2Fdp%2FB07MNBT68T&amp;sref=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2020/feb/26/nvidia-shield-tv-review-the-best-android-tv-box-with-brilliant-ai-upscaling" data-link-name="in body link">£109.99</a>, the Google Chromecast Ultra costs <a href="https://store.google.com/gb/product/chromecast_ultra" data-link-name="in body link">£69</a> and the Apple TV 4K costs <a href="http://go.theguardian.com/?id=114047X1572903&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.apple.com%2Fuk%2Fshop%2Fbuy-tv%2Fapple-tv-4k&amp;sref=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2020/feb/26/nvidia-shield-tv-review-the-best-android-tv-box-with-brilliant-ai-upscaling" data-link-name="in body link">£179</a>.</p><h2 class="">Verdict</h2><p class="css-38z03z">The original Nvidia Shield has long been the power user’s Android TV streaming box of choice, and realistically the only one I could recommend. But with its redesign as a hide-away tube and with a new, much more user-friendly and smartly designed remote, the new Shield TV is not only the best streaming box for power users, but one of the very best for regular people too – right up there with the Apple TV 4K and Amazon Fire TV Stick 4K.</p><p class="css-38z03z">On most fronts it beats or matches everything else, be it support for the latest Dolby Atmos, Vision and HDR standards, app support or even the built-in 4K Chromecast support. But it is the impressive AI upscaling that is the killer feature. If you predominantly watch HD content from Netflix, Amazon, YouTube, Google Play or BBC iPlayer et al on your 4K TV then the Shield TV is the box to buy.</p><p class="css-38z03z">The only fly in the ointment is a lack of the Apple TV or BT Sport apps in the Google Play Store on Android TV, but at least the latter can be Chromecast to the Shield TV from your phone or tablet. Only the Apple TV 4K has a wider selection of apps than available on Android TV.</p><p class="css-38z03z">The Shield TV isn’t cheap, coming in at £150, but it’s fast and feature-packed, will be supported for a long time and has one of the best remotes you can buy.</p><span class="css-1j0th6e"><blockquote>
<p><strong>Pros: </strong>AI upscaling, Android TV, fast, bloat-free, Dolby Vision, Dolby Atmos, long support, space-saving design, excellent remote, built-in 4K Chromecast, Google Assistant, GeForce Now</p>
<p><strong>Cons:</strong> fairly expensive, no BT Sport or Apple TV apps</p>
</blockquote></span><h2 class="">Other reviews</h2><ul class="css-38z03z">
